      <h3>Key Notes</h3>
      
      <ul>
      <li>This is only a simulation. Even if you are already working, you can earn full-time level income selling part-time.</li>
      
      <li>Commission is counted based on <strong>units installed</strong>, not just units ordered.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2>When is Commission Counted?</h2>
      
      <p>Commission is calculated <strong>only when the units are installed within the same month</strong>. </p>
      
      <p>Even though the order is made on the same month, but if the installation is in the next month then the sales is counted as "Net" on the next month.</p>
      
      <p><strong>Example Situations:</strong></p>
      
      <ul>
      <li><strong>Scenario 1:</strong> You close 10 units in August, and <strong>all 10 units are installed in August</strong> -&gt; Full commission counted in August.</li>
      
      <li><strong>Scenario 2:</strong> You close 10 units in August, but <strong>only 8 units are installed in August</strong> -&gt; Commission in August is only for 8 units. The remaining 2 units are counted in September.</li>
      </ul>
      
